Okay I want you all to see what made me start to 180 from Rust.

Here's some code I wrote, figure, if I can't make a graph, I can't use a language.
```struct SaturatedEdge&lt;T1, T2&gt;{
    from: T1, to: T1, wt: T2,
}
struct Edge&lt;T&gt;{
    from: T, to: T,
}
trait SimpleGraph&lt;T&gt; {
    fn addNode(&amp;self, e: T);
}
struct Graph&lt;T&gt;{
    nodes: i64, adj: Vec&lt;Vec&lt;T&gt;&gt;,
}
impl SimpleGraph&lt;T&gt; for Graph&lt;T&gt;{
    fn addNode(&amp;self, e: Edge&lt;T&gt;) {
        self.adj[e.from].push(<http://e.to|e.to>);
    }
}```
Here's how someone fixed it.
```trait SimpleGraph&lt;T&gt; {
    fn add_node(&amp;mut self, e: T);
}
impl&lt;T&gt; SimpleGraph&lt;T&gt; for Graph&lt;T&gt;
    where T:Copy, usize: From&lt;T&gt;
    {
    fn add_node(&amp;mut self, e: T) {
        self.adj[usize::from(e)].push(e);
    }
}```
Basically my brain exploded. I don't think I am at a place where I can think like this right now(&amp;mut is fine but the Copy, usize thing is :exploding_head::ahhhhhhh:)

